	(104, 7, 27, '<p style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: helvetica; color: #000000;"><strong>Regulamento</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: helvetica; color: #000000;">1- A inscri&ccedil;&atilde;o inclui: coffee break, material did&aacute;tico e certificado.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><br /><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: helvetica; color: #000000;">2- A realiza&ccedil;&atilde;o do Curso est&aacute; condicionada a um n&uacute;mero m&iacute;nimo de inscritos. A ABGE se reserva o direito de reagendar o curso at&eacute; 10 dias da data programada. Ap&oacute;s reagendamento, n&atilde;o se atingindo esse n&uacute;mero m&iacute;nimo, o curso ser&aacute; cancelado e o dinheiro, advindo das inscri&ccedil;&otilde;es, devolvido aos profissionais inscritos, ap&oacute;s a confirma&ccedil;&atilde;o do recebimento pela institui&ccedil;&atilde;o financeira e sem qualquer &ocirc;nus &agrave; ABGE.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><br /><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: helvetica; color: #000000;">3- Formas de pagamento:</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: helvetica; color: #000000;">&bull;&nbsp;Boleto banc&aacute;rio &ndash; as inscri&ccedil;&otilde;es pagas com boleto banc&aacute;rio ser&atilde;o confirmadas somente ap&oacute;s a quita&ccedil;&atilde;o do boleto.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: helvetica; color: #000000;">&bull;&nbsp;Cart&otilde;es de Cr&eacute;dito &ndash; Pelo site Sistema Pagseguro.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: helvetica; color: #000000;">&bull;&nbsp;Nota de empenho &ndash; dever&atilde;o ser encaminhadas at&eacute; 5 dias antes do curso.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><br /><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: helvetica; color: #000000;">4- Cancelamentos de inscri&ccedil;&atilde;o: Em caso de desist&ecirc;ncia, a solicita&ccedil;&atilde;o de cancelamento da inscri&ccedil;&atilde;o ser&aacute; aceita somente por escrito no e-mail: <a style="color: #000000;" href="mailto:atendimento@abge.org.br">atendimento@abge.org.br</a>, at&eacute; um dia antes da realiza&ccedil;&atilde;o do evento. As inscri&ccedil;&otilde;es canceladas ap&oacute;s esta data n&atilde;o ser&atilde;o reembolsadas. O reembolso, quando devido, corresponder&aacute; a 80% do valor pago e ser&aacute; efetuado ap&oacute;s o t&eacute;rmino do evento.</span><br /><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: helvetica; color: #000000;">A ABGE abre a possibilidade do valor do curso ficar de cr&eacute;dito para a inscri&ccedil;&atilde;o em um curso de igual ou menor valor.</span></p>', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2014-12-15 18:39:18', NULL),
	(103, 7, 24, '<p style="text-align: left;"><span style="color: #000000; font-size: 12pt; font-family: helvetica;"><strong>Bibliografia</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><span style="color: #000000; font-size: 12pt; font-family: helvetica;">1 - Brady, B.H.G. and Brown, E.T., Rock Mechanics for Underground Mining. George Allen &amp; Unwin, 1985;<br /><br />2 &ndash; Hoek, E. and Brown, E.T., Underground Excavations in Rock. The Institution of Mining and Metallurgy, London, 1980;<br /><br />3 &ndash; Tunnel Engineering Handbook, 2nd Ed., Editors Bickel, J.O.; Kuesel, T.R. and King, E.H. Chapman &amp; Hall, 1996;<br /><br />4 &ndash; Hoek.E.; Kaiser, P.K. and Bawden, W.F., Support of Underground Excavations in Hard Rock, Balkema/Rotterdam/Brookfield, 1995;<br /><br />5 - Grimstad, E. and Barton, N., Updating of The Q-System for NMT<br />Proc. Of Int. Symp.&nbsp; On Sprayed Concrete &ndash; Modern Use of Wet Mix Sprayed Concrete for Underground Support, Fagernes, 1993 (Eds Kompen, Opsahl and Berg. Norwegian Concrete Association, Oslo;<br /><br />6 &ndash; Lowson, A.R. and Bieniawski, Z.T., Critical Assessment of RMR based Tunnel Design Practices: a Practical Engineer&acute;s Approach. Rapid Excavation &amp; Tunneling Conference, June 2013, Washington DC;<br /><br />7 &ndash; Russo, G. An Update of The &ldquo;Multiple Graph&rdquo; Approach for the Preliminary Assessment of the Ecavation Barhaviour in Rock Tunneling. Tunneling and Underground Space Technology 41 (2014), p. 74-81;<br /><br />8 &ndash; Improved Longtudinal Displacement Profiles for Convergence Confinement Analysis of Deep Tunnels;<br /><br />9 - Rock-Support Interaction analysis for tunnels in weak rock masses, site da Rocsciente: http://www.rocscience.com/hoek/corner/12_Tunnels_in_weak_rock.pdf<br /><br />10 &ndash; Support for very weak rock associated with faults and shear zones;<br /><br />11- Underground works in Hard Rock Tunnelling and Mining;<br /><br />11 &ndash; Rock Mechanics Challenges in Underground Construction and Mining.<br /><br /></span></p>', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2015-02-11 12:24:24', NULL),
